Habibou Barrow was bitten by a dog on Sunday and died on his way to hospital in the Gambian capital, Banjul. PRETORIA - The eight-year-old son of Gambia s President-elect Adama Barrow has been killed by a dog.Barrow is not there for his son's funeral. He's sheltering in neighbouring Senegal as he waits for Yayha Jammeh to stand down as president. Habibou Barrow was bitten by a dog on Sunday and died on his way to hospital in the Gambian capital, Banjul.The president-elect s media team has confirmed the news to Freedom Newspaper, a local Gambian news portal.Barrow went to Dakar in Senegal on Sunday at the request of the Ecowas chairperson Ellen Johnson Sirleaf.Senegalese President Macky Sall agreed to host Barrow until his inauguration on Thursday when he will be escorted by some African leaders to the event.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)